Objective: Create a nutcracker for macamadamia nuts that is useable by anyone.
Constraints and Input Parameters: It takes 222.18 kg of strength to crack a macamadamia nut; average grip strength for a woman is 30kg. This design may also use an actuator instead of a hand.
Approach: The first step was to design a nutcracker for a person to use, and then update it if it was not feasible. Finding the moments about point A would yiepld a ratio of applied force to pivot A to the nut center of mass to pivot of 7.4
This means that for every inch the macamadamia nut is away from the pivot, the applied force must be 7.4 inches away. 
